1 Install npm first by npm install, to verify version npm --v
2 Install typescript globally by npm install -g typescript, to verify version tsc --v
3 Set env variables in 3 fiels according to the need
  3.1 .env.example to .env.development or .env.test

4.Package.json
  ðŸ“¦ What is package.json?
      Itâ€™s the manifest file for a Node.js project.
      Contains metadata: project name, version, scripts, dependencies, etc.
      Required if you want to install packages with npm or yarn.
  >npm init
     This starts an interactive wizard asking questions (name, version, description, entry point, etc.).
     At the end, it generates a package.json.   
  or
  > npm init -y
     Instantly creates a package.json with sensible defaults.
    
5.Update package.json with needed scripts and dependencies,(Node Module is getting created now)
  > npm install  -->to install all dependencies
  > npm install express -> to install specific node packagae
  > npm install --save-dev playwright  --> to speifc dev only not require in prod,packahe.json categorzie accordingly
  > npm install -g typescript --> install globally
  Note:To uninstall npm uninstall dotenv zod

